public class SpecialToken {
    public static String thirdToken(String str) {
        StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(str);
        String token = null;
        int count = 0;
        while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
            token = st.nextToken();
            count++;
            if (count == 3) {
                return token;
            }
        }
        return null;
    }
}
```
<<<explanation>>>: The nextToken() method of the StringTokenizer class returns the next token from the string. The tokens are delimited by delimiters. The StringTokenizer class is a simple yet powerful tool for breaking up a string into tokens.
